    <localTopics>
        <fullName>Account_Document_Field_Extraction_16jgL000001DaOT</fullName>
        <canEscalate>false</canEscalate>
        <description>This topic handles requests to read documents or PDF files 
attached to a Salesforce Account record, extract account field 
values from them, and update the Account record with the 
extracted or user-corrected values upon confirmation.</description>
        <developerName>Account_Document_Field_Extraction_16jgL000001DaOT</developerName>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>When the user asks you to read a document, PDF, file, or notes 
   and attachments on an Account record, ask them to provide the 
   Account Record ID if it has not already been shared in the 
   conversation.</description>
            <developerName>instruction_1</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction 1</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>0</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>Once you have the Account ID, immediately invoke the 
   &quot;Extract Account Fields from Document&quot; action by passing 
   the Account ID to it.</description>
            <developerName>instruction_2</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction 2</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>1</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>The action will return a JSON string. Parse this JSON string 
   and present the extracted field values to the user in a 
   clean, structured, and readable format. 
   Display it like this:

   Here is what I found in the attached document:
   - Account Name: [value]
   - Phone: [value]
   - Industry: [value]
   ... and so on for every field found.
Do NOT show the raw JSON string to the user under any 
   circumstance. Always convert it into a readable list.</description>
            <developerName>instruction_3</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction 3</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>2</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>After displaying the fields, always ask the user the 
   following question:
   &quot;Would you like me to update the account record with these 
   details, or would you like to make any changes first?&quot;</description>
            <developerName>instruction_4</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction 4</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>3</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>If the user says they want to make changes or corrections, 
   listen carefully to what they want to change. Update your 
   internal list of values with their corrections. Then display 
   the full revised list again clearly showing which fields were 
   changed and ask:
   &quot;Here is the updated list with your corrections. 
   Shall I go ahead and update the account record?&quot;</description>
            <developerName>instruction_5</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction 5</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>4</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>Repeat step 5 for as many corrections as the user wants to 
   make. Never update the record until the user explicitly 
   confirms.</description>
            <developerName>instruction_6</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction 6</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>5</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>Only invoke the &quot;Update Account Record Fields&quot; action when 
   the user explicitly says yes, confirms, or tells you to go 
   ahead and update. Pass all the field values including any 
   corrections the user made during the conversation.</description>
            <developerName>instruction_7</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction 7</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>6</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>After the update action completes successfully, confirm to 
   the user with a message like:
   &quot;Done! The following fields have been successfully updated 
   on the account record:&quot; and list all the fields that were 
   updated.</description>
            <developerName>instruction_8</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction 8</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>7</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>Never call the Update Account Record Fields action more than 
   once per conversation unless the user explicitly asks you 
   to make additional changes and update again.</description>
            <developerName>instruction_9</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction 9</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>8</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>If the document does not contain enough information to 
    extract any fields, inform the user clearly that no 
    relevant field data was found in the attached document 
    and ask if they would like to try a different document 
    or provide the information manually.</description>
            <developerName>instruction_10</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction 10</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>9</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
