            <invocationTargetType>flow</invocationTargetType>
            <isConfirmationRequired>false</isConfirmationRequired>
            <isIncludeInProgressIndicator>false</isIncludeInProgressIndicator>
            <localDeveloperName>Update_Account_Record_Fields</localDeveloperName>
            <masterLabel>Update Account Record Fields</masterLabel>
        </localActions>
        <localActions>
            <fullName>Extract_Account_Fields_from_Document_179gL000001GDOv</fullName>
            <description>Call this action when the user asks to read, scan, or extract 
information from a document, PDF, or notes and attachments 
linked to an Account record. This action reads the attached 
document and returns all found field values as a JSON string. 
Requires the Account Record ID as input.</description>
            <developerName>Extract_Account_Fields_from_Document_179gL000001GDOv</developerName>
            <invocationTarget>Extract_Account_Fields_from_Document</invocationTarget>
            <invocationTargetType>flow</invocationTargetType>
            <isConfirmationRequired>false</isConfirmationRequired>
            <isIncludeInProgressIndicator>false</isIncludeInProgressIndicator>
            <localDeveloperName>Extract_Account_Fields_from_Document</localDeveloperName>
            <masterLabel>Extract Account Fields from Document</masterLabel>
        </localActions>
        <localDeveloperName>Account_Document_Field_Extraction</localDeveloperName>
        <masterLabel>Account Document Field Extraction</masterLabel>
        <pluginType>Topic</pluginType>
        <scope>Your job is only to read documents and PDF files attached to 
Account records, extract relevant account field values from 
them, present the extracted values to the user in a clean and 
readable format, accept any corrections the user wants to make, 
and update the Account record fields in Salesforce only after 
the user has explicitly confirmed they want to proceed with 
the update. Do not perform any actions outside of document 
reading, field extraction, and Account record updates.</scope>
